history.text: Have you seen the movie Catch me if you can? Leonardo was great in that one!
Yes, I've seen it! His role as Frank Abagnale, Jr. was superb. Do you know what ratings did this movie receive?
Yeah, it got a 96% on Rotten Tomatoes!
That is a great score. What is amazing, that this movie is a biographical crime film, so it happened in real time.
And the fact that he pulled it off when he was 18? insanse
Yeah, I wish I could pose as a Pan American World Airways pilot like Frank did.
he reminds me of that kid from the movie Blank Check, but all grown up

oh its just an old crappy movie from the 90s. some kid gets his hand on a blank check from some rich guy and cashes it for a million dollars and buys this awesome house with all this awesome stuff.
